# 3. トラブルは突然に

Manager: This is it. Please watch your step.
Kohane: Th-Thank you.
An: Wow, this hotel's gorgeous...!
Kohane: The entrance alone is so glamorous...
An: I can't believe Uncle Taiga booked us such a luxurious hotel.
Manager: Please wait here. I'll be over at the check-in counter.
An & Kohane: Okay! Thank you.
Akito: You okay, Toya?
Toya: Yes... I feel much better compared to before...
An: Hmm... Yeah, you're definitely not as pale as you were on the plane.
Kohane: Let us know if you need to take a rest, Aoyagi.
Toya: I apologize for making you all worry about me like this. I was doing fine for most of the flight...
Toya: But I became curious just before we landed, and ended up opening my eyes.
Kohane: Haha. I understand why you wanted to take a look.
Akito: Yeah, I guess.
Akito: Still, actually standing here in the city is...
Toya: Frankly, I'm moved.
Toya: I've visited a number of other countries...
Toya: Each time I set foot on the soil and see the sights with my own eyes, I feel this same rush of excitement.
Toya: Seeing everyone go about their day, all the sounds, their conversations, the atmosphere... They hit you all at once.
Akito: Yeah, just standing here, I feel like all my senses are being bombarded with all sorts of information.
An: Yeah, me too! Is this what it means to get a feel for the city?
Kohane: *Nod* We're really here... In the United States of America.
An: Man, I'm so excited now!
An: Let's head up to our room, put our bags down and check out some of the shops nearby... Wait, huh?
Toya: What's wrong, Shiraishi?
An: Something isn't right...
Akito: What do you mean?
An: Look over at the check-in counter.
An: The manager and the clerk both look really concerned.
Kohane: Oh, you're right... Do you think there's something wrong?
Toya: We're too far away to hear what they're saying...
An: Oh no! The manager put his hands on his head.
Akito: I've got a bad feeling about this... Oh, here he comes.
Manager: I'm so sorry, everyone... The thing is...
Toya: We don't have a reservation?
Manager: Yes, I'm incredibly sorry...
Manager: Taiga said he'd book his favorite hotel, but he accidentally made a reservation for one month from now...
Akito: Seriously...?
An: Wait, he used to do stuff like that all the time when I was a kid and we went on trips together!
An: This one time, we were gonna stay at an inn with hot springs, but he ended up booking a campsite deep in the mountains. We had to pitch our own tents and practically live off the land.
Akito: You're kidding, right?
An: No, I'm serious! He's always really careless when it comes to these sorts of things...
Kohane: Wait, would it be possible for us to book some different rooms?
Manager: Unfortunately, they're all booked up.
Manager: I even checked all the hotels nearby...
Toya: Taiga's event is happening soon.
Toya: People from all over the world must be looking forward to seeing it. In other words, we're not alone, and finding a place to stay won't be easy.
Toya: (The sun will be setting in a few hours... We should probably avoid wandering around after dark.)
Toya: (But what do we do in this situation...?)
Shuji: <I see... You let me know if you ever need anything.>
Toya: ...
Toya: (He has his performance to worry about, so I'd rather not bother him.)
Toya: (But...)
Akito: So, we wait here?
Toya: Yes, he should be here soon.
Manager: I'll be excusing myself once I've handed you all over.
Manager: Once I've managed to find a hotel for tomorrow onwards, I'll let you all know...
Toya: Thank you. We really appreciate it.
An: Still, I'm so glad that we managed to find shelter for tonight!
Kohane: Me too! Thank you for doing this, Aoyagi.
Toya: No, I didn't do anything... My brother did all the work.
Akito: Still, we would've been up a creek if you hadn't gotten a hold of your brother.
An: Yeah! Would you mind thanking him for us?
Toya: Not at all. I'll let him know later.
Kohane: Oh, also...
Kohane: The person coming to get us isn't your brother, is he?
Toya: No, he's out of state for a performance at the moment.
Toya: In his message, he said, “Someone I respect very much is coming to get you.”
???: “Ah, there you all are.”
